Whip|+0|20|+3|Bludgeoning|15 ft.|Small|4|2 lb.|Exotic|A whip can strike targets up to 15 feet away. You can use it to make <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Trip">trip</a> attacks and to <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Disarm">disarm</a> opponents with a +2 bonus, like the <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Trip">Improved Trip</a> and <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Disarm">Improved Disarm</a> feat. Its benefits stack if you have those feats. You do not add your Strength to damage done with a whip.|
Wrist Knife|+1|20|+3|Slashing|-|Tiny|4|1 lb.|Exotic|The wrist knife has an oval blade made from a flat piece of iron. It is worn around the wrist like a bracelet. The outside edge of the weapon is sharpened, while the inside is protected with leather to avoid harming the wearer.</p><p>A wrist knife never has to be readied, which makes it an excellent weapon for use in a <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a>. In addition, it can be worn while holding an item or wielding a weapon without penalty. It cannot be used in the same hand as a shield. A wrist knife can be used in conjunction with the <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Strike">Improved Strike</a> feat. It provides the user with a +10 to resist <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Disarm">disarm</a> attempts.</p><p>A wrist knife can be used in combination with <a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Armoured%20Gloves">armoured gloves</a>, incurring no attack penalty due to the gloves' bulkiness.|
